Former President Soeharto, his family, cronies, and senior officials enjoyed privileges beyond the Soeharto family.
Companies and foundations under Soeharto's control amassed significant wealth.
Soedjono defended Soeharto's right to privacy as a private citizen.
Estimates put Soeharto's family fortune at $20 billion, with foreign media valuing it at $40 billion.
The new government vows to combat corruption and nepotism.
Investigations into Soeharto's alleged illicit wealth stashed overseas are ongoing.
Public pressure mounts for accountability, with mass demonstrations demanding justice for Soeharto's alleged financial misconduct.
